column49: I unfortunately don't like that parents have to order online and can not turn money into teachers. I sent out the flyers to my parents for September and only 1 person ordered 1 book. It is unfortunate that most of our student population come from families that don't have checking accounts or credit cards. I absolutely loved the opportunity for my students to order books but I don't think with this new process it will work for our families. I also feel like the prices have increased too much which is another reason no one probably didn't ordered books. Due to these issues it is really a waste of my time if no one is going to order books. This truly makes me sad since I have been ordering for 26 years. If any ideas or suggestions I would love to hear them. Thanks!

column49: After all of these years using scholastic book clubs I am very disappointed with the book club flyers that the parents would receive.
